Notes: TCNJ loss its second in a row despite 17 from Theresa DiMedio and 15 from
Laura Mala. MSU was led by a double-double from Jasmine Batts who had 17
points and 13 boards. No. 3 TCNJ will be at No.2 Richard Stockton on Thursday,
February 27 at 7 p.m. in the first round of the NJAC Playoffs.
